label.value: regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation.

label.value: positive regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation.

label.value: negative regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation.

label.value: regulation of ferroptosis

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of ferroptosis.

label.value: negative regulation of ferroptosis

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of ferroptosis.

label.value: vesicle-mediated intercellular transport

value.value: A cellular transport process in which transported substances are moved in extracellular vesicles between cells; transported substances are enclosed in the vesicle lumen or located in the extracellular vesicle membrane.

label.value: regulation of placenta blood vessel development

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of placenta blood vessel development.

label.value: positive regulation of placenta blood vessel development

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of placenta blood vessel development.

label.value: negative regulation of placenta blood vessel development

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of placenta blood vessel development.

label.value: hippocampal neuron apoptotic process

value.value: Any apoptotic process that occurs in a hippocampal neuron.

label.value: regulation of hippocampal neuron apoptotic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the occurrence or rate of cell death by apoptotic process in hippocampal neurons.

label.value: positive regulation of hippocampal neuron apoptotic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell death by apoptotic process in hippocampal neurons.

label.value: negative regulation of hippocampal neuron apoptotic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell death by apoptotic process in hippocampal neurons.

label.value: cellular detoxification of aldehyde

value.value: Any process carried out at the cellular level that reduces or removes the toxicity of an aldehyde. These may include transport of aldehydes away from sensitive areas and to compartments or complexes whose purpose is sequestration of the toxic substance.

label.value: cellular response to aldehyde

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an aldehyde stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of animal organ morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of animal organ morphogenesis.

label.value: negative regulation of animal organ morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of animal organ morphogenesis.

label.value: regulation of lipid transporter activity

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of lipid transporter activity.

label.value: positive regulation of lipid transporter activity

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate, or extent of lipid transporter activity.

label.value: negative regulation of lipid transporter activity

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate, or extent of lipid transporter activity.

label.value: regulation of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation.

label.value: positive regulation of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation.

label.value: negative regulation of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation.

label.value: myotube cell migration

value.value: The orderly movement of a myotube cell from one site to another, often during the development of a multicellular organism. Myotubes are multinucleated cells that are formed when proliferating myoblasts exit the cell cycle, differentiate, and fuse.

label.value: regulation of myotube cell migration

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of myotube cell migration.

label.value: positive regulation of myotube cell migration

value.value: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of myotube cell migration.

label.value: negative regulation of myotube cell migration

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of myotube cell migration.

label.value: cellular anatomical entity

value.value: A part of a cellular organism that is either an immaterial entity or a material entity with granularity above the level of a protein complex but below that of an anatomical system. Or, a substance produced by a cellular organism with granularity above the level of a protein complex.

label.value: DNA synthesis involved in mitochondrial DNA replication

value.value: Any DNA biosynthetic process that is involved in mitochondrial DNA replication.

label.value: regulation of glutamatergic neuron differentiation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glutamatergic neuron differentiation.

label.value: negative regulation of glutamatergic neuron differentiation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of glutamatergic neuron differentiation.

label.value: positive regulation of glutamatergic neuron differentiation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of glutamatergic neuron differentiation.

label.value: somatostatin binding

value.value: Binding to somatostatin, a polypeptide hormone involved in regulating pancreatic alpha and pancreatic beta cells and controlling growth hormone secretion as well as many other functions. Somatostatin is produced by several cell types including pancreatic delta cells. There are several different mature forms of somatostatin.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection

value.value: A prolongation or process extending from a cell and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label.value: proton export across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of hydrogen ions (protons) from inside a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the extracellular region.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Formation of a prolongation or process extending and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label.value: regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: negative regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: positive regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of plasma membrane bounded cell projections.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization

value.value: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a plasma membrane bounded prolongation or process extending from a cell, e.g. a cilium or axon.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the anatomical structures of a plasma membrane bounded cell projection are generated and organized.

label.value: regulation of macrophage proliferation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of macrophage proliferation.

label.value: positive regulation of macrophage proliferation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of macrophage proliferation.

label.value: negative regulation of macrophage proliferation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of macrophage proliferation.

label.value: regulation of gastric emptying

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of any gastric emptying process, the process in which the liquid and liquid-suspended solid contents of the stomach exit through the pylorus into the duodenum.

label.value: negative regulation of gastric emptying

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of any gastric emptying process, the process in which the liquid and liquid-suspended solid contents of the stomach exit through the pylorus into the duodenum.

label.value: positive regulation of gastric emptying

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of any gastric emptying process, the process in which the liquid and liquid-suspended solid contents of the stomach exit through the pylorus into the duodenum.

label.value: neuron projection cytoplasm

value.value: All of the contents of a plasma membrane bounded neuron projection, excluding the plasma membrane surrounding the projection.

label.value: glucagon processing

value.value: The formation of mature glucagon by proteolysis of the precursor proglucagon.
